 her head.\r\n\r\nPropped up by fury upon the stiff couch,\r\n\r\nshe twitches and twists towards the light\r\n\r\nthat flickers for her in horrendous unrest\r\n\r\n(pathetic fallacy of the industrial age.)\r\n\r\nThe words she distilled in her Private Practice:\r\n\r\nIt’s not that I resent my dear mother.\r\n\r\nIt’s not for my brothers I wish the worst.\r\n\r\nIt’s only you, Father, who I need to block:\r\n\r\nYou’re an old Sigmoid colon that I’m fit to burst.','Daddy\'s Girl (Anger Becomes Electra)','','publish','open','open','','daddys-girl-anger-becomes-electra','','','2013-11-05 20:08:39','2013-11-05 20:08:39','',0,'http://belgianwaffler.com/?p=99',0,'post','',0),(100,1,'2013-11-05 20:08:13','2013-11-05 20:08:13','','Daddy\'s Girl (Anger Becomes Electra)','','inherit','open','open','','99-revision','','','2013-11-05 20:08:13','2013-11-05 20:08:13','',99,'http://belgianwaffler.com/?p=100',0,'revision','',0),(101,1,'2013-11-05 20:09:41','2013-11-05 20:09:41','I envy those who flick on and off,\r\n\r\ncan intercept the neuro-transmitted notes of\r\n\r\nnonsense reverberating along old vertebrae,\r\n\r\nrattling off the rails.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSome switch with no glitches\r\n\r\nfrom the broadcasts transmuted\r\n\r\nby the voice of unreason/ unable;\r\n\r\nspinal cords in accord with good vibrations.\r\n\r\nwhilst on a loop one crackled chorus\r\n\r\ntimidly twitches my tangled cables.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nErsatz Goebbels gnarls in my ear;\r\n\r\ncan’t tune in, tune out to Radio Stable.\r\n\r\nBrain scans abnormal, cerebral shit-smear-\r\n\r\ncampaigns. Ruthless. My eye against \'I\':\r\n\r\nboth gnawing toothless.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI envy those who go about business\r\n\r\nwhile I flail about in total stillness,\r\n\r\nfailing to disrupt the black noise.\r\n\r\nEnvy those who travel around Italy\r\n\r\nwith their back-packs on, serotonin intact\r\n\r\nwithout the constant yackity-yack of\r\n\r\nstrangers gathering in their synaptic fields:\r\n\r\nclowning